<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEYMOUR B. PEARLMAN; FOUNDER OF CENTERS FOR BLIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seymour B. Pearlman, 74, a longtime Los Angeles attorney and co-founder with 
his wife of Therapeutic Living Centers for the Blind. The organization was 
founded in 1975 to provide housing, education and lifetime care for the 
developmentally disabled blind. His efforts led to the founding of homes and 
education centers throughout the San Fernando Valley. In Burbank on May 28 of a 
blood ailment. 
</P>
