<TEXT>
<P>
The French Z-Peugeot squad won a team time trial at the midway point of the 
Milk Race bicycling event, allowing team leader Olaf Lurvik of Norway to take 
the overall leadership of the race in Blackpool, England. 
</P>
<P>
Z-Peugeot riders completed the 34.5-mile seventh stage from Southport to 
Blackpool in 1 hour 13 minutes 12 seconds to edge Britain's amateur team by 
five seconds. 
</P>
<P>
The victory allowed Lurvik, who had started the day in second place overall, to 
jump past British amateur Nigel Bishop into the overall lead with a time of 
24:38.43. Bishop is second, 14 seconds behind. 
