<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tim McCarver, who has worked on ABC's national baseball telecasts since 1984, 
will join Brent Musburger as a commentator when CBS takes over baseball in 
1990. 
</P>
<P>
CBS outbid ABC and NBC, which have traditionally carried baseball, and will pay 
$1.1 billion over four years for the rights. 
</P>
<P>
McCarver, a former major league catcher, also broadcasts New York Mets games on 
WWOR-TV in New York. 
