<P>
GAY ACTIVISTS CHEER KOOP AT FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gay rights activists, once among departing Surgeon General C. Everett Koop's 
harshest critics, applauded him as a hero at a walk attended by 18,000 people 
seeking to raise money to fight AIDS. 
</P>
<P>
The crowd on Boston Common roared its approval Sunday and chanted: "Koop, Koop, 
Koop" as the 72-year-old public health chief, who will step down from his post 
this year, approached the podium. 
</P>
<P>
When the crowd refused to stop applauding, Koop quipped: "I could have used 
that during my eight years in Washington." 
</P>
