<TEXT>
<P>
Driving for Dollars: What may be one of the best jobs on the East Coast was 
uncovered recently when Boston Edison Co. sought a rate increase: Budget 
documents revealed that the chairman's chauffeur is paid $60,000 a year. Not 
even Donald J. Trump's driver makes that much and he's been with the real 
estate tycoon for 10 years. The chauffeur's salary is among the $185,000 that 
the utility spent last year to provide company officials with cars and 
chauffeurs. News of the expenditures comes as the company seeks an $85-million 
rate increase, or about $50 more a year from its customers. 
</P>
