<P>
Sears Boycott Threatened: The American Postal Workers Union has demanded that 
Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. remove mini-post offices set up in 11 of its stores 
and threatened to boycott the retailer if it ignored the request. "We view this 
as a menace to postal jobs, postal workers and the general public," union 
President Moe Biller said. A Sears spokeswoman said the Chicago-based retailer 
planned to continue the one-year pilot program at least through October. She 
said she was unaware of plans to expand the program. Biller said he was told by 
Postal Service officials that as many as 100 Sears stores may soon have the 
counters. 
