<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: SANTA ANA; 
</P>
<P>
RECEPTION FOR MEXICAN CONSUL GENERAL SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A reception for Romeo Flores Caballero, Mexico's consul general in Los Angeles, 
will be held today in the City Council chambers and followed by a press 
conference to announce the name of the new consul general assigned to the 
county. 
</P>
<P>
Later in the day, Flores will speak at a luncheon sponsored by the Hispanic 
Chamber of Commerce of Orange County and other hosts at Rancho de Mendoza 
Restaurant in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
The consul general will talk about Mexico's recent dramatic economic step that 
allows foreign companies to own up to 100% of many businesses in Mexico and to 
invest in other industries from which they had been barred. 
</P>
<P>
Before the luncheon, Flores will tour Santa Ana's downtown, including the 
Fiesta Marketplace, and visit Roosevelt Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
For information, call the Hispanic Chamber of Commerce at (714) 953-4289. 
</P>
</TEXT>
