<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Endowment for the Arts has awarded the Newport Harbor Art Museum 
$4,900 to buy and install earthquake-resistant metal shelving in the art 
storage vault and $4,000 to support maintenance of the museum's permanent 
collection. In March, the NEA awarded the museum $20,000 to help finance the 
purchase of "Rondo," (1968-69) an installation by James Turrell. 
</P>
