<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
NEIGHBORS BLOCK LOPEZ CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Neighbors of the Lopez Canyon Landfill blocked garbage trucks from entering the 
dump today, for the third time this year. 
</P>
<P>
About 30 protesters, who live in Lake View Terrace, Pacoima and Kagel Canyon, 
said they believe that the city-operated landfill is hazardous to their health. 
The Los Angeles Bureau of Sanitation denies that the dump is dangerous. 
</P>
<P>
Today's protest was aimed at a meeting of the California Waste Management Board 
scheduled for Friday in Los Angeles. At that meeting, board members will review 
the dump's operating permit, which is out of date. 
</P>
<P>
The protest ended after about an hour, when Los Angeles police officers 
threatened to arrest protesters if they did not disperse. 
</P>
</TEXT>
