LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran must withdraw the late Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini's death edict against 
author Salman Rushdie before relations between Tehran and London can return to 
normal, Britain said today. 
</P>
<P>
"We shall be looking to Iran to renounce publicly the use or threat of the use 
of terrorism and violence," a Foreign Office spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Rushdie has been in hiding under police guard since Khomeini's order last 
February. Iran broke diplomatic ties with Britain last March in the furor that 
followed Khomeini's call on Muslims to kill Rushdie because his novel, "The 
Satanic Verses," blasphemed Islam. 
