</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FEATHERWEIGHT TITLE FIGHT DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MILAN, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The World Boxing Organization featherweight title fight between Italian 
champion Maurizio Stecca and Venezuelan challenger Levy Mayor has been 
postponed one week to June 16. 
</P>
<P>
The bout was originally scheduled at Milan's Palatrussardi arena Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Stecca's manager, Umberto Branchini, said today that a delayed recognition of 
the title fight by the Italian Boxing Federation caused the postponement. 
</P>
<P>
"We were informed that the authorization will be given by June 16," Branchini 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Italian officials initially had opposed Mayor, claiming that he was not a boxer 
of international level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
